MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of Specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-05 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following: 1) Performing front office receptionist duties (e.g., greet, screen, check-in visitors) to provide customer service;
2) Schedule internal/external customers visiting or calling;
3) Preparing agendas notifying participants of time and place of scheduled meetings;
4) Arranging the meetings and conferences; maintaining and monitoring the appointment schedules for management;
5) Managing travel arrangements (e.g., travel documents, travel orders, security clearance, hotel transportation reservations) to maintain stall punctuality for events and
6) Gathering materials, composing correspondences into final form to review for correct spelling, grammar, and punctuation for use in reports, emails, presentations, speeches, etc. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management website:
https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.
